The '''Deutsch-Arabische Gesellschaft''' (DAG; The German-Arabian Association) is an association founded in 1966 to strengthen German-Arabian relations in political, environmental, and cultural areas.
The president of the organisation is [[Peter Scholl-Latour|Prof. Dr. Peter Scholl-Latour]], Author and TV-Editor (†16.08.2014), before the FDP politician [[Jürgen Möllemann]] till 2003. The ambassadors to the Arabian countries are also members of the company.
