'''[[Homelessness]] in [[Vatican City]]''' is a minor social issue. A shelter has been established just outside the Vatican walls and was opened by [[Pope Francis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/06/11/pope-francis-homeless-shelter_n_7562672.html|title=Pope Francis To Open 30-Bed Homeless Shelter Steps From Vatican Walls|first=Rosie Scammell Religion News|last=Service|date=11 June 2015|publisher=}}</ref> The shelter is called “Gift of Mercy” (“Dono di Misericordia”).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://religionnews.com/2015/10/16/surprise-pope-francis-stops-by-vaticans-new-homeless-shelter/|title=Surprise! Pope Francis stops by Vatican’s new homeless shelter|publisher=}}</ref>

The pope has also organized for showers to be built in the public toilets and allowed a deceased homeless man to be buried in the Vatican.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/vaticancityandholysee/11435074/Homeless-man-to-be-buried-inside-the-Vatican-for-the-first-time-in-Holy-See-history.html|title=Homeless man to be buried inside the Vatican for the first time in Holy See history|publisher=}}</ref>

