{{one source|date=October 2018}} The '''Inter-parliamentary Coalition for Combating Antisemitism''' (ICCA) is an international coalition of Parliamentarians from around the world that work together to combat [[antisemitism]]. Among its goals is the understanding and awarneness of [[new antisemitism|modern antisemitism]] and ways to combat it on a global scale.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.antisem.org/about-us/|title=Account Suspended|website=www.antisem.org}}</ref>
The first annual conference of the ICCA was held in [[London]], [[England]] in cooperation with the British Government in 2009 and produced the [[London Declaration on Combating Antisemitism]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.antisem.org/london-declaration/|title=Account Suspended|website=www.antisem.org}}</ref> Former British Prime Minister [[Gordon Brown]] was the first world leader to sign the Declaration.<ref>http://ukinisrael.fco.gov.uk/en/news/?view=News&id=14159560</ref> It has subsequently been signed by several additional Prime Ministers across the globe and more than 600 Parliamentarians worldwide.{{citation-needed|date=February 2018}}
The second annual conference was held in [[Ottawa]], [[Canada]] in association with the [[Canadian Parliamentary Coalition to Combat Antisemitism]] and the Canadian Government on November 7–9, 2010.<ref>http://www.antisem.org/2010-conference/</ref>
The ICCA established an informal [[working group]] on antisemitism in the European Parliament, which produced a report into hate on the internet and established a working group on hate on the internet including all major internet industry players.{{citation-needed|date=February 2018}}
==Steering Committee== The Steering Committee of the ICCA consists of:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.antisem.org/steering-committee/|title=Account Suspended|website=www.antisem.org}}</ref>
*[[John Mann (British politician)|John Mann]], Member of the [[British Parliament]] * Petra Bayr, Member of the Austrian Parliament * [[Irwin Cotler]], Member of the [[Canadian Parliament]] * Petra Pau, Vice-President of the German Bundestag * [[Chris Smith (New Jersey politician)|Christopher Smith]], Member of [[United States Congress]] * Cecilia Wikstrom, Member of the European Parliament, Sweden * Emanuelis Zingeris, Member of the Lithuanian Parliament * Evariste Kalisa, Member of the Rwandan Parliament, Vice-President of the Chamber of Deputies
