[[File:1L259 radar.jpg|thumb|Zoopark-1]] '''Zoopark-1''' 1L219 is a [[Counter-battery radar]] system developed jointly by [[Almaz-Antey]] for the [[Russian Armed Forces]]. It is a mobile [[Passive electronically scanned array]] [[radar]] based on a tracked [[MT-LBu]] chassis for the purpose of enemy [[field artillery]] acquisition. The system can detect moving ground targets at a distance of up to 40 kilometers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://defence-blog.com/army/russian-artillery-units-used-new-zoopark-1m-radar-systems-for-the-first-time.html|title=Russian artillery units used new Zoopark-1M radar systems for the first time|first=Dylan|last=Malyasov|website=Defence Blog}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.almaz-antey.ru/en/catalogue/millitary_catalogue/1219/1242/1329|title=Zoopark-1|website=Almaz – Antey}}</ref>
